          "date": "2014-10-07 12:49:00.000000000",
          "tz": 330
        },
        "subject": "LU-5604 obd: Porting missing FAIL_IDs",
        "message": "LU-5604 obd: Porting missing FAIL_IDs\n\n\"Unified request handlers\" related commits (i.e. LU-3467,\nLU-2145) removed assignment/conditional \"if\" statements\nrelated to following macros:\n\n- OBD_FAIL_OST_LDLM_REPLY_NET\n- OBD_FAIL_LDLM_REPLY\n- OBD_FAIL_OST_CREATE_NET\n- OBD_FAIL_LDLM_ENQUEUE\n\nThese marcos were used by some tests and as those marcors\nare removed it broke the tests. So in this patch porting\nabove mention macros appropriately to fix those tests.\n\nXyratex-bug-id: MRP-2071\nSigned-off-by: Rahul Deshmukh <rahul_deshmukh@xyratex.com>\nChange-Id: Ib4252c32b282d90a8b8af378fdbcc0e77ae149e6\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
